primary.context: Caller wanted to book a two-bedroom and a one-bedroom unit for June.
primary.detail: The AI agent correctly identified that booking reservations is out of scope and transferred the caller to the concierge department.

steps: Caller requested to speak with a representative to book their week.
Agent attempted a transfer but returned when no agents were available.
Agent verified caller's identity (phone, name, state).
Caller specified they wanted to book a two-bedroom and a one-bedroom unit.
Agent identified a discrepancy in the account records regarding unit sizes.
Agent initiated a second transfer to an ownership specialist/concierge.

clarifications.note: Agent clarified which unit to book due to record mismatch.

corrections.note: User corrected agent regarding unit size (two-bedroom vs one-bedroom).

actions.detail: Initial transfer failed due to no agents available.
Pulled up account details for The Berkley Las Vegas.
Transferred to concierge for booking and unit size dispute.

insights.summary: The caller wanted to book specific units for June. Since reservations are out of scope, the AI agent correctly verified the caller and transferred them to the concierge department.
insights.verbatim: I would like to book my two bedroom and my one bedroom in June. If possible.
